column6: Description
Melted animal fat that can lubricate the Bear Trap squeaky joints.\n\n- Setting a Bear Trap is silent.
A scratched and worn brace made of thick, cured animal skin.\n\n- You are no longer caught in your own Bear Traps, they are automatically disarmed instead.

These padded jaws are meant to restrain, not to wound. - Bear Traps immobilise <#e2ce97>Survivors without damaging them. - Grants <#e8c252>100% bonus <#e2ce97>Bloodpoints for trapping <#e2ce97>Survivors.
Protective padded leather gloves.\n\n- Increases the Setting speed of the Bear Trap by <#e8c252>+30%.

A replacement kit for Bear Trap which changes the usual dual spring system to four coil springs, adding a great amount of strength to the Bear Traps hold.\n\n- Increases the Disarm time of the Bear Trap by <#e8c252>+33 %.
An old rusted can containing damp coffee grounds.\n\n- Increases the strength of the <#e2ce97>Haste Status Effect after setting a Bear Trap by <#e8c252>+5 % .
Jaws with long teeth that dig further into the flesh than a conventional Bear Traps.\n\n- <#e2ce97>Survivors who escape from Bear Traps suffer from the <#e2ce97>Deep Wound Status Effect.

These replacement trap jaws have saw-like blades, causing awful open wounds when they snap. - <#e2ce97>Survivors injured by a Bear Trap suffer from the <#e2ce97>Haemorrhage Status Effect until fully healed. <#e2ce97>"Like a predatory beast, it can smell and track blood."
A block of wax used to lower friction and facilitate movement in mechanical parts.\n\n- Increases the Rescue and Escape times of the Bear Trap by <#e8c252>+33 %.

A specialised set of tools used to fasten Bear Traps to ensure their effectiveness. - Increases the Rescue and Escape times from the Bear Trap by <#e8c252>+25 %. - Increases the Setting speed of the Bear Trap by <#ff8800>+50 %.

These Bear Trap jaws are covered with crusty and volatile rust spots, making injuries particularly difficult to heal.\n\n\t-Survivors injured by a Bear Trap suffer from the Mangled Status Effect for 70 seconds.
A secondary coil keeps the Bear Trap functional in times when the primary coil becomes unusable.\n\n- Increases the Disarm time of the Bear Trap by <#e8c252>+50 %.
A black, matte and sticky substance that when applied to Bear Traps, makes them far less noticeable.\n\n- Darkens the Bear Trap.
A cured leather waist bag. Large and sturdy to transport hunting equipment. - Increases the number of carried Bear Traps by <#e8c252>+1.

When used with the Bear Trap, the stone sharpens its blades. The razor-sharp blades inflict deep wounds aimed at bleeding the victim as fast as possible. - <#e2ce97>Survivors caught in a Bear Trap, who free themselves, are inflicted with the <#e2ce97>Dying State.
A clear oil that makes handling the Bear Trap's spring more hazardous.\n\n- Resetting a Bear Trap reveals the <#e2ce97>Aura of the last Survivor to have disarmed it for <#e8c252>5 seconds.
A high tension spring that snaps back into place after being stretched.\n\n- Automatically resets the Bear Trap <#e8c252>2 seconds after a Survivor escaped from it.
A crude leather sack suitable for foraging. - Causes all Bear Traps to be carried in your inventory at the beginning of the Trial. - You can no longer pick up any placed Bear Traps, only reset them.

Part sticky, part slippery, this grim liquid makes handling the Bear Traps spring more dangerous.\n\n- When a healthy Survivor disarms a Bear Trap, the Bloody Coil exacts its price, putting the Survivor into the <#e2ce97>Injured State.
Bear Traps sharpened with the sickly gleaming stone seem to gain a life of their own.\n\n- Automatically resets and arms a random disarmed Bear Trap every <#e8c252>30 seconds.

The Kunwulju symbol, representing the Realm of Fear, is finger-drawn out of soot on the body of the Bell.

<indent=10%>- Your <#e2ce97>Terror Radius<sprite=7></color> is no longer suppressed when Cloaked.</indent>
<indent=10%>- Grants <#e8c252>+100 %</color> bonus <#e2ce97>Bloodpoints<sprite=14></color> for Stalking and Surprise Attack Score Events.

The Khugwemuu symbol, representing the Spirit World, is finger-drawn out of soot on the body of the Bell.\n\n- Your <#e2ce97>Terror Radius and Red Stain are suppressed for another <#e8c252>6 seconds after uncloaking.

The Wonnug symbol, representing a peerless tracker, is finger-drawn out of soot on the body of the Bell.\n\n<indent=10%>- When Cloaked, <#e2ce97>Pools of Blood<sprite=3></color> appear to you in <#d41c1c>bright red</color>.

The Laokeye symbol, representing cunning, is finger-drawn out of soot on the body of the Bell.\n\n<indent=10%>- Breaking <#e2ce97>Breakable Walls<sprite=12></color> or <#e2ce97>Pallets<sprite=9></color> by any means, or performing the Damage Generator Action on incomplete <#e2ce97>Generators<sprite=6></color>, will cause you to automatically uncloak.

The Baikra-Kaeug symbol, representing ferocity, is finger-drawn in mud on the body of the Bell.\n\n- <#e2ce97>Survivors hit with a Surprise Attack suffer from the <#e2ce97>Blindness Status Effect for <#e8c252>60 seconds.
The Kratin symbol, representing quick passing, is finger-drawn in mud on the body of the Bell.\n\n- Reduces the Cloaking time by <#e8c252>-40 %.
The Kuntin-Takkho symbol, representing a rapid descent on a prey, is finger-drawn in mud on the body of the Bell.\n\n- Reduces the Uncloaking time by <#e8c252>-8 %.
The Ohuwe-Onmnea symbol, representing a howling storm, is finger-drawn in mud on the body of the Bell.\n\n- Increases your Movement Speed by <#e8c252>+5 % when Cloaked.

A Bell clapper made from a highly polished piece of bone.
Causes the sounds of the Wailing Bell to echo and warp chaotically.

<indent=10%>- <#e2ce97>Survivors<sprite=5></color> are unable to discern the distance and direction of the Wailing Bell.

The Baikra-Kaeug symbol, representing ferocity, is stamped in white ink on the body of the Bell.\n\n- <#e2ce97>Survivors hit with a Surprise Attack suffer from the <#e2ce97>Haemorrhage and <#e2ce97>Mangled Status Effects for <#e8c252>70 seconds.
The Kratin symbol, representing quick passing, is stamped in white ink on the body of the Bell.\n\n- Reduces the Cloaking time by <#e8c252>-60 %.

The Yiwarick symbol, representing dark synergy, is stamped in white ink on the body of the Bell.\n\n- Increases the Action speeds for breaking <#e2ce97>Breakable Walls and <#e2ce97>Pallets, damaging <#e2ce97>Generators, and vaulting <#e2ce97>Windows by <#e8c252>+40 % while Cloaked.
The Kuntin-Takkho symbol, representing a rapid descent on a prey, is stamped in white ink on the body of the Bell.\n\n- Reduces the Uncloaking time by <#e8c252>-10 %.
The Ohuwe-Onmnea symbol, representing a howling storm, is stamped in white ink on the body of the Bell.\n\n- Increases your Movement Speed by <#e8c252>+7 % when Cloaked.

The Kra-Frabai symbol, representing the Entity watching over us, is stamped in blood on the head of the Bell.

Unlocks hidden potential in your Aura-reading ability:

<indent=10%>- The <#e2ce97>Auras<sprite=13></color> of <#e2ce97>Survivors<sprite=5></color> are revealed to you within <#e8c252>8 metres</color> of your location when Cloaked.

The Yiwarick symbol, representing dark synergy, is stamped in blood on the body of the Bell.\n\n- Increases the Action speeds for breaking <#e2ce97>Breakable Walls and <#e2ce97>Pallets, damaging <#e2ce97>Generators, and vaulting <#e2ce97>Windows by <#e8c252>+60 % when Cloaked.
The Kuntin-Takkho symbol, representing a rapid descent on a prey, is stamped in blood on the body of the Bell.\n\n- Reduces the Uncloaking time by <#e8c252>-12 %.
The Ohuwe-Onmnea symbol, representing a howling storm, is stamped in blood on the body of the Bell.\n\n- Increases your Movement Speed by <#e8c252>+9 % when Cloaked.

The Kra-Frabai symbol, representing the Entity watching over us, ominously glows on the head of the Bell.

Unlocks hidden potential in your Aura-reading ability:

<indent=10%>- Reveals the Repair progression of <#e2ce97>Generators<sprite=6></color> via the intensity of their <#e2ce97>Aura<sprite=13></color> when Cloaked.
A simple coxcomb knotted rope wrapped around the bell clapper to muffle its sound. A malevolent Aura emanates from it. - Silences the Wailing Bell.

You get excited in anticipation of hooking your prey. When carrying a Survivor, you benefit from the following effects: - Increases your Movement speed by <#e8c252>6/<#199b1e>12/<#ac3ee3>18 %. - Increases your <#e2ce97>Terror Radius by <#e8c252>+12 metres. <#e2ce97>"At some point, the excitement of hooking one of us becomes more important than the desire to kill us."

Your great strength allows you to shred through your prey's defences. - Increases the Action speed of breaking <#e2ce97>Pallets and <#e2ce97>Breakable Walls, and damaging <#e2ce97>Generators by <#e8c252>10/<#199b1e>15/<#ac3ee3>20 %. <#e2ce97>"It is more than muscles. A dark power motivates the beast."

Your presence alone instils great fear. <#e2ce97>Survivors repairing or healing within your <#e2ce97>Terror Radius suffer from the following effects: - Increases the Trigger odds of <#e2ce97>Skill Check by <#e8c252>10 %. - Decreases the Success zone of <#e2ce97>Skill Checks by <#e8c252>40/<#199b1e>50/<#ac3ee3>60 %. <#e2ce97>"Its presence befalls us."

Like a hunting scent hound, you smell traces of blood at a great distance. - <#e2ce97>Pools of BloodIconStatusEffects bleedingIconStatusEffects bleeding are shown in <#d41c1c>bright red and can be tracked for <#e8c252>2/<#199b1e>3/<#ac3ee3>4 seconds longer than normal. <#e2ce97>"Pebbles shimmering in the moonlight; my life drips down in a trail so easy to follow."

Your acute tracking ability allows you to hone in on disturbances left by running <#e2ce97>Survivors. - The <#e2ce97>Scratch Marks left by <#e2ce97>Survivors spawn <#e8c252>slightly/<#199b1e>moderately/<#ac3ee3>considerably closer together. <#e2ce97>"Never stop moving and hope you're always two steps ahead of the beast." — Unknown, Notebook

You have a keen vision in the darkness of the night. - When blinded by any means, you are granted a <#e8c252>6/<#199b1e>8/<#ac3ee3>10 % <#e2ce97>Haste Status Effect for <#e8c252><#ac3ee3>10 seconds. <#e2ce97>"Shining in the darkest dark, his eyes pierce the night and sting your soul."
